{ rules: [
    { about: "growth",
      text: [
        "Statistics can be increased by improving racial powers, deepening background involvement of the player and learning a specialisation from a master.",
        "A specialisation level can be added to a relevant action besides the relevant statistic.",
        "Each background point, power or specialisation costs 2xp or 1 more for every point already learned.",
        "During the game new contacts and master can be found, but the XP cost still applies for learning specialisations and their maximal teacher level will be limited.",
        "The background can provide 2 items from their list, but for every more item more points needs to be spend in that background.",
        "New items can be found however they need to be transported by the players and their bulk will limit the number of things.",
        "Endurance is the default bulk that can be carried.",
        "A background also provides contacts with masters in the listed specialisations, but to learn into those more than 2 points also needs deeper background levels.",
        "It is impossible to learn the same thing or category directly after each other, so no two backgrounds or specializations increase back to back."
        "Each character starts with 6 things learned." ] },
    { about: "cards",
      text: [
        "Each power and most items allow a player cards.",
        "A scenario starts with the 8 default cards as the stock pile, there will also be a starting tension.",
        "As the players learn from the challenge they are facing, each player adds 2 cards from their character sheet to this pile.",
        "During the scenario a leader character can allow the group to add more cards or perhaps even remove cards.",
        "Each round a player picks two cards from the randomly shuffled stack and plays a card as an action.",
        "When the card depicts a statistic that is relevant for the action they want to perform they can add the statistics points they already have to the total."
      ] },
    { about: "aid each other",
      text: [
        "A player can aid another player by passing a card to them during their own turn, they can still play another card themselves later.",
        "When the other player accepts this card, they need to play at least that card themselves in their next turn.",
        "However this increases the tension of the scenario itself, allowing for more complications to arise within it.",
        "With more tension than 5 the cards player for the scene participants themselves add complications." ] },
    { about: "heroic action",
      text: [
        "Alternatively a player can put their complete hand on the table and add all statistics on them as a bonus to their actions.",
        "However they shuffle the cards and play them one by one, the special of the first card enhances their action, but the next complicates the scene and so on." ] },
  ]
  statistics: [
